Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.03,0:15:06.29,Default,Ouji,0,0,0,,Sakuragi used the \Nwest stairwell, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.41,0:15:10.67,Default,Saruta,0,0,0,,Why would she use \None so far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:13.69,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,She must've had a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:16.69,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,Takako said she saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.69,0:15:18.30,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,Sugiura Takako?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.84,0:15:20.72,Default,Mochizuki,0,0,0,,What did she see?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.58,0:15:23.06,Default,Ayano,0,0,0,,When Kouichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.98,0:15:38.91,Default,Nakao,0,0,0,,I honestly thought it \Nwouldn't happen this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.23,0:15:41.76,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,There are two possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.76,0:15:43.46,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,It's not happening this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.46,0:15:46.17,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,and Yukari's death \Nwas just a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.17,0:15:50.03,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,Or it started back in May.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.03,0:15:51.91,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,As the head of countermeasures,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.91,0:15:55.27,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,I can't rely on wishful thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.27,0:15:57.01,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,It'd be one thing \Nif it was just Yukari,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.01,0:15:59.76,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,but her mom died too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.76,0:16:03.71,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Is it because he broke the rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.71,0:16:09.19,Default,Nakao,0,0,0,,Why would they bring a new student to class 3, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.19,0:16:11.15,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,It was convenient for the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.15,0:16:15.42,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,The new principal still doesn't fully understand our situation.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.42,0:16:18.90,Default,Nakao,0,0,0,,Shouldn't the teachers \Nexplain it to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.90,0:16:23.74,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,They might have thought it was \Nbest to keep it among the students.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.46,0:16:26.83,Default,Nakao,0,0,0,,So even the teachers want \Nnothing to do with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.39,0:16:30.64,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,This is all because I was \Nabsent on his first day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:34.49,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,If I had warned him earlier, \Nthis wouldn't have happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.04,0:16:38.74,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,What's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.74,0:16:41.19,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,The question is, \Nwhat do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.19,0:16:44.47,Default,Nakao,0,0,0,,And how do we let him know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.47,0:16:48.44,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,It'll be difficult to \Nexplain it to him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:51.19,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,And explaining it poorly \Ncould be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:54.86,Default,Sugiura,0,0,0,,Like getting caught \Nin our own trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.86,0:16:58.79,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,This is a lot like the situation \Nthis class was in two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.11,0:17:04.33,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Does that mean we need \Nnew countermeasures?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.04,0:17:49.45,Default,Boy1,0,0,0,,That's what I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.45,0:17:50.96,Default,Boy2,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.35,0:18:07.84,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,H-Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.84,0:18:08.82,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.82,0:18:09.60,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.60,0:18:12.35,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Don't "uh" me. Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.39,0:18:17.78,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I've been trying to \Ncall you all week.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.78,0:18:18.76,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why aren't you answering?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.76,0:18:21.85,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Sorry! I was going \Nthrough some stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.85,0:18:24.68,Default,Teshigarara,0,0,0,,Besides, you were sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.30,0:18:28.95,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You promised \Nyou'd tell me in June.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.48,0:18:33.21,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You mentioned \N"the first year", too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.21,0:18:34.42,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What exactly happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.76,0:18:37.56,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,Just hang on. Okay, Sakaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.56,0:18:39.84,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I did promise that, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.84,0:18:41.47,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.47,0:18:43.48,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,The situation has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.48,0:18:45.80,Default,Teshigawara,0,0,0,,That's right! The \Nsituation has changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.21,0:18:52.35,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Normally, it's up to the head of \Ncountermeasures to handle this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.35,0:18:57.07,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,But because this guy acted on \Nhis own, things got complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.07,0:18:57.56,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.25,0:19:00.32,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You want me to pretend he \Nnever made that promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.32,0:19:03.36,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Yes. As a favor to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.36,0:19:06.89,Default,Izumi,0,0,0,,Rather, to the entire class.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.44,0:19:11.77,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.77,0:19:16.39,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,But you said it's dangerous to involve myself with things that don't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.39,0:19:17.99,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What did you mean by that?
